<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Shower1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Shower,</orth> subst. a short fall of rain: <bibl n="shak. ven 66" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 75.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 75, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.124.12" default="NO" valid="yes">124, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 4.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. IV, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.2.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 2, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.35" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.337" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 337</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.156" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.1.7" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 III, 1, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 2.2.180" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 2, 180</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.2.156" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 2, 156</bibl> <emph>(a s. of rain).</emph> Used of any thing falling fast and thick; of tears: <bibl n="shak. luc 796" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 796</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 1.1.125" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 125.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.50" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.145" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.5.85" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 85</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 5.3.161" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. V, 3, 161</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.5.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 5, 39</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.2.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 2, 44</bibl>. of blood: <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.43" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 43</bibl>. of pebbles: <bibl n="shak. h8 5.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 4, 60</bibl>. <cit><quote>a s. of gold,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.5.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 5, 45</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>in the great s. of your gifts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 5.1.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. V, 1, 73</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>made a s. and thunder with their caps and shouts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 2.1.283" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 1, 283</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--s of oaths,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.245" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 245</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>